FBIS4-65886 "drweu101_j_94003" FBIS-WEU-94-101 Daily Report 24 May 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY Predicts `Pro-Israeli' Government Predicts `Pro-Israeli' Government LD2405185294 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1758 GMT 24 May 94 LD2405185294 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext Italian BFN [Text] "This Italian government will be the most pro-Israeli in the past 20 years". These were the words with which Foreign Minister Antonio Martino who is currently visiting Washington, sought to reassure the Jewish-American community. At the next G-7 meeting Martino will ask for condemnation of "the ongoing Arab economic boycott of Israel." Martino met earlier with U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher, who said "he has a lot of faith in the government that resulted from the elections: we are ready to work together."
